summary: TGEV, a member of Alphacoronavirus genus, is a single-stranded, positive-sense RNA virus. it has eight functional genes that code for four structural proteins. TGEV has four nonstructural genes. nucleotide sequence of strain AYU has 99.1%, 99.2%, 99.6%, 98.3%, 98.2%, 98.5%, and 97.8% homology. a small reading frame (AUGAAAUCA) consisting of three codons lies in the 5′ end, stretching from nt 117 to nt 125.
